<subSubSection id="99C7F65092B0FF3102A028DF002DBEBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F6C9B09EEDB3B6038F47A4E12970A9B4" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7868A1AF2178628E3745219FCE89AB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<bibRefCitation id="0D01625691BB7EE88DDEABD4B00F5143" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13904" author="Purcell, WF" journalOrPublisher="Annals of South African Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 32" refId="B146" refString="Purcell, WF, 1898. Description of new South African scorpions in the collection of the South African Museum. Annals of South African Museum 1: 1 - 32" title="Description of new South African scorpions in the collection of the South African Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13904" volume="1" year="1898">Purcell (1898)</bibRefCitation>
listed 21 specimens (4 males, 6 females, 11 juveniles) from Clanwilliam in the type series located in the South African Museum (Cape Town). The ZMH specimens are a gift to the Hamburg Museum but they are probably not part of the original series as explained by 
<bibRefCitation id="F81C0EE10453310196EF42A805AA180C" author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. One lectotype male and 20 paralectotypes (three males, four females, one subadult male, four subadult females and eight juveniles) from the series of syntypes held at the SAMC were designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="34DFB188793673CFB0481FA89C2016E8" author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001</bibRefCitation>
: 31). Given that the number of specimens at the SAMC matches the original data by Purcell, it is doubtfull that the five ZMH specimens are types (
<bibRefCitation id="A687357B9828C823838FE4409ABADF5C" author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 47).
</paragraph>
